shared_text:
Bering Strait School District
February 22, 2019 at 1:38 AM ·

The Wildlife Conservation Society's Arctic Beringia program is seeking student applicants for a paid summer position as a videographer from July 15-25, 2019. This is an amazing opportunity to travel to the Icy Cape area, south of Wainwright, where the birds nest, and spend time documenting in the field with Dr. Rebecca McGuire, Frank Chythlook, and two other student assistants.
See attached poster for more information, and please pass the word along to students and young adults that might be interested! The poster says the deadline is February 15th, but they still have one slot open.
text:
Bering Strait School District
February 22, 2019 at 1:38 AM ·

The Wildlife Conservation Society's Arctic Beringia program is seeking student applicants for a paid summer position as a videographer from July 15-25, 2019. This is an amazing opportunity to travel to the Icy Cape area, south of Wainwright, where the birds nest, and spend time documenting in the field with Dr. Rebecca McGuire, Frank Chythlook, and two other student assistants.
See attached poster for more information, and please pass the word along to students and young adults that might be interested! The poster says the deadline is February 15th, but they still have one slot open.
